<i>-♪ Yeah ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Walk with me ♪</i>

26:47.709 --> 26:50.792
<i>♪ Ooh, it's gonna be ♪</i>

26:50.875 --> 26:54.000
<i>-♪ Walk with me ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Gonna be, gonna be all right ♪</i>

26:54.083 --> 26:55.500
<i>♪ Everything ♪</i>

26:55.583 --> 26:59.500
<i>-♪ And I will walk with you ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Is gonna be all right ♪</i>

26:59.583 --> 27:03.542
<i>♪ Walk with me, and I will walk with you ♪</i>

27:03.625 --> 27:04.583
[Hayes] Aaron?

27:04.667 --> 27:06.583
-Hey, Doc.
-Happy to report

27:06.667 --> 27:08.417
he pulled through surgery
like a champ, OK?

27:08.500 --> 27:10.291
Dr. Grey's settling him into the ICU now.

27:10.417 --> 27:11.542
And w-what about his kidney?

27:11.625 --> 27:13.792
OK. We did have to remove
part of his kidney,

27:13.875 --> 27:15.250
but it's still functioning,

27:15.333 --> 27:16.959
so we'll monitor him closely,
but it's promising.

27:17.041 --> 27:19.625
OK. Thank you so much,
Dr. Hayes. Thank you.

27:19.709 --> 27:21.583
Once the anesthesia wears off,
we'll set you up with a tablet

27:21.667 --> 27:23.083
-so you can chat, OK?
-Thank you!

27:26.166 --> 27:27.000
[DeLuca] Mr. Lee?

27:28.125 --> 27:29.542
These are Kayden's doctors.

27:29.625 --> 27:30.834
[Steve] How is he?

27:31.667 --> 27:33.083
Is Mrs. Lee here?

27:33.166 --> 27:35.458
She's outside. One second.

27:35.542 --> 27:37.458
-Let me get her on the phone.
-[Maggie] No, no, we sh--

27:37.709 --> 27:39.166
[Teddy] Let's-- Let's go and talk to her.

27:39.834 --> 27:40.667
Why?

27:44.709 --> 27:45.542
No.

27:46.875 --> 27:47.875
Oh, God.

27:49.041 --> 27:49.875
No.

27:52.125 --> 27:53.583
Just tell me he's alive.

27:54.375 --> 27:56.125
Just that much, because...

27:56.834 --> 27:58.583
I can't go all the way to my wife

27:59.208 --> 28:00.709
if I don't even know that.

28:02.750 --> 28:03.750
[crying] No.

28:06.041 --> 28:06.875
No!

28:08.709 --> 28:10.417
He can't be.

28:10.500 --> 28:11.959
Not my baby boy.

28:14.208 --> 28:17.166
[sobbing] Oh, not my baby boy.

28:18.041 --> 28:21.625
[sobbing]

28:21.709 --> 28:24.250
No! [crying]

28:24.333 --> 28:25.625
It's OK. Come on.

28:26.458 --> 28:27.417
I got you.

28:28.417 --> 28:29.333
I got you.

28:30.417 --> 28:32.834
[crying]

28:45.250 --> 28:49.375
So, that's your report--
that the world is on fire?

28:49.458 --> 28:51.625
[Bailey]
I think it's an accurate summation.

28:51.709 --> 28:54.125
What, you-- you want me
to give you the long version?

28:54.208 --> 28:57.542
Well, Koracick's $100,000 order

28:57.625 --> 28:59.208
was nothing but booties.

28:59.291 --> 29:01.667
We are losing people. We're losing money.

29:01.750 --> 29:04.875
But we'll keep showing up until we win.

29:05.000 --> 29:06.750
-End of report.
-[door opens]

29:06.834 --> 29:09.250
Look, I get that Richard humiliated you

29:09.333 --> 29:11.750
when he sent you away after his surgery.

29:11.834 --> 29:12.750
So what?

29:12.834 --> 29:15.709
You humiliated him
when you bought his hospital.

29:15.834 --> 29:18.834
You have both done
incredibly hurtful things.

29:18.917 --> 29:22.333
But he is someone who can
help you through this nightmare

29:22.583 --> 29:24.083
and bring you some joy,

29:24.291 --> 29:26.542
which is something we all need
more of right now.

29:26.625 --> 29:30.583
And it's only too late
if you decide it's too late!

29:30.792 --> 29:32.166
There are people dying!

29:32.250 --> 29:34.583
There are children dying!

29:34.667 --> 29:36.750
There's a worldwide pandemic!

29:36.834 --> 29:38.417
But you are still alive.

29:38.500 --> 29:40.125
And I am sorry that I'm yelling right now,

29:40.208 --> 29:42.208
but it really does feel good,

29:42.291 --> 29:43.709
especially when it's the truth!

29:44.166 --> 29:47.625
[claps hands]
Also an accurate summation.

29:47.709 --> 29:48.625
Schmitt?

29:49.333 --> 29:51.333
[Levi] Oh, thank God.
That was really uncomfortable.

29:52.000 --> 29:53.917
[Bailey chuckles]

30:01.333 --> 30:03.125
[crying]

30:07.709 --> 30:08.959
[door opens]

30:09.041 --> 30:10.250
[clears throat]

30:10.333 --> 30:13.333
Sorry. I just, um-- [clears throat]

30:15.458 --> 30:17.250
I just really wanted that kid to live.

30:17.333 --> 30:19.041
Yeah. We all did.

30:19.125 --> 30:21.959
Oh, OK, so you're on Owen's side, too.

30:22.041 --> 30:23.166
I guess that makes everyone.

30:23.250 --> 30:25.125
You think they should be on <i>your </i>side?

30:26.041 --> 30:28.166
I think everyone should just
mind their own business.

30:28.250 --> 30:29.834
Having your life fall apart is hard enough

30:29.917 --> 30:31.333
without everyone's judgment.

30:32.542 --> 30:33.375
[sighs]

30:34.709 --> 30:38.500
Let me guess.
You just followed your heart.

30:40.125 --> 30:43.083
Well, this is where your heart led you,
and it's no one's fault but your own.

30:43.834 --> 30:46.792
You had a beautiful life,
a beautiful family,

30:46.875 --> 30:49.083
and you blew it up with a butt dial?

30:50.375 --> 30:53.542
Do you have any idea how
humiliating that is for Owen?

30:53.625 --> 30:55.041
It's not my fault that Alex left you,

30:55.333 --> 30:57.625
but if you want to take that out
on me, then OK. Fine.

31:01.583 --> 31:03.041
You never made a mistake?

31:03.834 --> 31:05.750
You never hurt someone that you love?

31:06.959 --> 31:08.917
[voice breaking]
You never tried to sabotage

31:09.000 --> 31:12.542
your own happiness because easy and happy

31:12.625 --> 31:14.959
are so unfamiliar to you?

31:15.834 --> 31:18.417
They're so foreign
that you can't even live with it.

31:19.041 --> 31:22.250
I love Owen, and I broke us,

31:22.333 --> 31:24.709
and that feeling is unbearable.

31:24.792 --> 31:27.458
So you can judge me all you want
or you can take a break,

31:27.542 --> 31:30.500
because I'm doing enough judging
of myself for the both of us.

31:32.125 --> 31:35.208
Have you said all of that to him?

31:35.291 --> 31:36.917
I tried, but he doesn't want to listen.

31:38.125 --> 31:40.125
Try harder.

31:45.208 --> 31:49.000
[door opens]

31:49.083 --> 31:50.291
[door shuts]

32:00.125 --> 32:01.333
I got paged.

32:05.959 --> 32:08.583
Am, uh, I supposed to guess
what you wanted?

32:12.041 --> 32:14.709
Hey, Catherine. I-I got your page.

32:14.792 --> 32:16.625
I guess you, uh...

32:16.709 --> 32:18.417
[sighs] you heard about the delivery.

32:18.500 --> 32:23.250
Tom, sometimes a crisis
proves bigger than any one man.

32:23.333 --> 32:25.041
This one has proved bigger than you.

32:26.625 --> 32:29.166
You'll stay on as neuro attending,

32:29.250 --> 32:32.625
but I'm accepting your resignation
as chief of chiefs,

32:32.709 --> 32:34.500
effective immediately.

32:36.041 --> 32:38.583
[sighs] Are-- Are you firing me?

32:39.500 --> 32:42.375
[chuckles]
And you expect me to-- to stay?

32:42.458 --> 32:44.709
Uh, yeah. N-No, thanks.

32:44.792 --> 32:47.125
I-I can get a job anywhere I want.

32:47.208 --> 32:49.417
And, what, broadcast your sexual escapades

32:49.500 --> 32:51.041
in someone else's OR?

32:51.792 --> 32:54.542
Tommy, word gets around.

32:55.667 --> 32:57.041
This is a new world.

32:58.208 --> 32:59.834
If I were you, I'd take the win.

33:01.125 --> 33:02.083
[sighs]

33:14.375 --> 33:18.625
Dr. Webber, I'm hoping that you

33:18.709 --> 33:21.834
will accept his job as chief of chiefs

33:22.542 --> 33:26.709
and my apologies for everything
I've done to hurt you.

33:27.792 --> 33:29.375
I am so sorry.

33:29.667 --> 33:30.959
<i>♪ Amen ♪</i>

33:33.875 --> 33:34.750
Well...

33:34.834 --> 33:35.875
<i>♪ Amen ♪</i>

33:35.959 --> 33:40.083
...I guess we need to get
our hands on some COVID tests.

33:40.250 --> 33:41.208
<i>♪ Amen ♪</i>

33:41.291 --> 33:43.667
Why? A-Are you feeling poorly?

33:43.959 --> 33:46.000
<i>No, I-I feel fine. Never felt better.</i>

33:47.500 --> 33:49.291
<i>I just want to make sure it's safe</i>

33:49.375 --> 33:52.208
<i>to do all the things</i>
<i>I want to do with you.</i>

33:52.291 --> 33:53.500
<i>♪ Somebody that they all know ♪</i>

33:54.583 --> 33:55.750
<i>♪ I double-check my phone ♪</i>

33:55.834 --> 33:57.333
[Catherine chuckles]

33:57.500 --> 33:59.709
<i>♪ No new messages, no missed calls ♪</i>

33:59.792 --> 34:03.333
<i>♪ Everybody needs somebody</i>
<i>To hold them too close ♪</i>

34:03.417 --> 34:07.750
<i>♪ I need a little mercy, mercy ♪</i>

34:09.083 --> 34:11.250
<i>♪ I need a little mercy, mercy ♪</i>

34:11.333 --> 34:12.750
[clears throat]

34:12.834 --> 34:14.125
Andrew.

34:14.333 --> 34:16.625
What? I'm tagging you out, right?

34:16.709 --> 34:19.500
You know, I-I pulled off
this incredible surgery,

34:19.583 --> 34:22.917
and I sort of got a second wind,
so I think I can stay.

34:23.000 --> 34:25.875
You know, someone once told me
that sleep's important.

34:25.959 --> 34:27.834
-Mm. I should try it sometime.
-Mm-hmm.

34:27.917 --> 34:29.291
<i>♪ Devil's not in the details,</i>
<i>He's on the front page ♪</i>

34:29.375 --> 34:31.083
Is there any specific patient
you want me to check in on?

34:31.166 --> 34:33.291
-I can do it.
-It should be me.

34:34.041 --> 34:36.333
OK. You know that friend
who told me about sleep?

34:36.417 --> 34:38.500
She also told me that
I wouldn't be much use to anyone

34:38.583 --> 34:41.166
if I didn't take care of myself.

34:41.250 --> 34:42.667
She's a friend now, huh?

34:43.166 --> 34:45.458
She saved my life, so...

34:46.125 --> 34:48.792
she's whatever she wants to be to me.

34:48.917 --> 34:50.250
<i>♪ I need some mercy, mercy ♪</i>

34:50.333 --> 34:52.917
-OK. 1702--
-Mm-hmm.

34:53.000 --> 34:55.792
If she decompensates at all,
please call me.

34:55.875 --> 34:57.208
I don't care what time it is.

34:57.291 --> 34:58.375
OK. You have my word.

34:58.458 --> 34:59.375
Thanks.

34:59.458 --> 35:00.333
<i>♪ Mercy ♪</i>

35:01.417 --> 35:03.041
-Good luck out there.
-Thanks.

35:03.125 --> 35:06.000
<i>♪ Mercy, mercy, no murcielago ♪</i>

35:06.083 --> 35:08.041
<i>♪ Just a Nissan low on gas ♪</i>

35:08.125 --> 35:10.417
<i>♪ Thank God for every time</i>
<i>He saved my ass ♪</i>

35:10.500 --> 35:12.291
<i>♪ Like back when we was on the Internet ♪</i>

35:12.375 --> 35:14.125
<i>♪ But we never copped nothin' ♪</i>

35:14.208 --> 35:15.750
[Levi scoffs]
Not sure what you're looking for,

35:15.834 --> 35:17.417
but we probably don't have it.

35:17.500 --> 35:19.458
<i>♪ Moral of the story</i>
<i>You can't take it with you ♪</i>

35:19.625 --> 35:22.875
<i>♪ Moral of the story</i>
<i>Everybody needs something or somebody ♪</i>

35:22.959 --> 35:23.875
<i>♪ Everybody needs a lil mercy ♪</i>

35:23.959 --> 35:24.917
What are you doing?

35:25.000 --> 35:25.875
Look...

35:27.208 --> 35:28.625
I was a terrible boyfriend,

35:28.709 --> 35:30.917
and I get it if you say no, but...

35:31.959 --> 35:34.792
my thinking is that you just
need some stress relief.

35:34.875 --> 35:37.959
And while I couldn't provide you

35:38.041 --> 35:42.000
with the love and the affection
that you deserved...

35:42.083 --> 35:43.959
<i>♪ Mercy ♪</i>

35:44.041 --> 35:45.458
...I can provide you with that.

35:45.542 --> 35:47.041
<i>♪ I need a little mercy ♪</i>

35:47.125 --> 35:48.083
Stress relief?

35:48.166 --> 35:49.166
<i>♪ Mercy ♪</i>

35:49.291 --> 35:50.667
Stress relief.

35:50.750 --> 35:51.625
<i>But...</i>

35:51.709 --> 35:54.083
<i>♪ I need a little mercy, mercy ♪</i>

35:54.166 --> 35:55.583
...can we leave my mask on?

35:55.667 --> 35:56.583
<i>♪ I don't wanna talk to God ♪</i>

35:56.667 --> 35:58.083
That's not what I want to take off.

35:58.166 --> 36:00.625
<i>♪ I just wanna be free ♪</i>

36:00.709 --> 36:02.041
<i>♪ Mercy ♪</i>

36:02.125 --> 36:03.375
[packages clatter]

36:03.458 --> 36:05.125
<i>♪ Mercy ♪</i>

36:09.041 --> 36:11.083
[laughing] I'm serious.

36:11.166 --> 36:13.375
The next time you feel overwhelmed,

36:13.458 --> 36:15.000
<i>just start screaming.</i>

36:15.083 --> 36:17.458
<i>It really-- </i><i>It really took a load off.</i>

36:17.542 --> 36:19.166
[chuckles]

36:24.875 --> 36:26.291
<i>Everything OK?</i>

36:26.375 --> 36:29.041
<i>There's just a tent here</i>
<i>that wasn't here this morning.</i>

36:31.917 --> 36:32.834
<i>Surprise.</i>

36:33.417 --> 36:35.083
What? What are you
talking about? What are...

36:38.208 --> 36:39.333
<i>Did you do this?</i>

36:39.417 --> 36:40.834
Well, sort of, yeah.

36:40.917 --> 36:43.542
I-I bought it, but your family
did all the labor.

36:43.625 --> 36:47.417
<i>You work harder than anybody</i>
<i>I know, and you need your rest.</i>

36:47.500 --> 36:48.333
<i>So I thought this way,</i>

36:48.417 --> 36:50.166
<i>you could see your family</i>
<i>whenever you wanted</i>

36:50.250 --> 36:52.083
without having to sleep on the floor.

36:54.250 --> 36:55.291
<i>Oh, baby.</i>

36:56.250 --> 36:58.333
[laughing] Oh, my--

36:58.417 --> 36:59.250
Oh, my--

37:00.458 --> 37:02.792
Oh, my God!

37:03.250 --> 37:07.000
This is amazing! Oh! I l--

37:08.125 --> 37:09.375
What was that?

37:09.542 --> 37:10.542
You were about to say it.

37:10.625 --> 37:12.291
<i>Shut up. I was not.</i>

37:12.834 --> 37:15.542
<i>But if Kingsley is there,</i>
<i>I have something to say to him.</i>

37:15.625 --> 37:19.125
-[laughs]
<i>-And I know you don't like </i><i>camping, but...</i>

37:19.208 --> 37:24.625
<i>No, no. You know, </i><i>it turns out</i>
<i>when it's just a-a tent </i><i>in a backyard...</i>

37:24.709 --> 37:26.500
<i>camping's kind of sexy.</i>

37:27.250 --> 37:28.542
-Oh, really, now?
<i>-Mm-hmm.</i>

37:28.625 --> 37:29.625
<i>♪ And into my heart ♪</i>

37:29.709 --> 37:32.291
Oh. I got to decon first.

37:32.375 --> 37:35.250
<i>♪ I wanna drive you wild, wild, wild ♪</i>

37:35.333 --> 37:37.792
Wait a minute. You really gonna
strip and not let me watch?

37:38.917 --> 37:39.959
[chuckles]

37:40.041 --> 37:41.834
<i>♪ I wanna love you ♪</i>

37:42.875 --> 37:43.709
<i>OK.</i>

37:43.792 --> 37:46.458
<i>♪ For miles and miles ♪</i>

37:47.500 --> 37:51.208
<i>♪ We can go slow, we don't need to rush ♪</i>

37:51.291 --> 37:55.041
<i>♪ I'll take the wheel</i>
<i>Make you feel every touch ♪</i>

37:55.125 --> 37:59.041
<i>♪ I wanna drive you wild, wild, wild ♪</i>

37:59.125 --> 38:01.834
You got all the kids to bed
while I was building that tent?

38:02.959 --> 38:04.500
Can you forget all my birthdays?

38:05.667 --> 38:06.959
[chuckles]

38:07.041 --> 38:09.166
I know. It's pathetic.

38:09.250 --> 38:10.333
I couldn't even light the candle

38:10.417 --> 38:12.291
because I can't find anything
in this house that makes fire,

38:12.375 --> 38:14.208
because we hid it all away from Bailey.

38:14.291 --> 38:15.417
<i>♪ We'll get there tonight ♪</i>

38:15.500 --> 38:17.709
I love it. Thank you.

38:18.709 --> 38:20.250
They accidentally sent gluten-free.

38:20.333 --> 38:21.583
I'm so sorry.

38:21.667 --> 38:22.667
<i>♪ You set me on fire ♪</i>

38:22.750 --> 38:23.792
Mmm!

38:24.000 --> 38:26.375
[sighs] I really am sorry I forgot.

38:27.375 --> 38:28.500
Are you kidding?

38:29.125 --> 38:31.166
There were no major meltdowns...

38:32.166 --> 38:34.417
I got to have sex, and...

38:34.500 --> 38:35.542
...I got a donut.

38:35.625 --> 38:37.291
<i>♪ Wild, wild, wild ♪</i>

38:37.333 --> 38:39.583
The only guy who might be luckier

38:40.291 --> 38:42.625
is Scout Derek Shepherd Lincoln...

38:42.959 --> 38:44.291
<i>♪ I wanna love you for miles and miles ♪</i>

38:44.375 --> 38:46.500
...because he has the best mom
in the whole world.

38:47.834 --> 38:49.792
Now I've got to get a glass
of water, because this is--

38:49.875 --> 38:52.083
-They're terrible.
-It's terrible. Terrible. [clears throat]

38:52.166 --> 38:55.375
[Meredith] <i>As proud as we</i>
<i>surgeons are of our stitches,</i>

38:56.291 --> 38:58.667
<i>they aren't meant </i><i>to be a permanent fix.</i>

38:59.583 --> 39:01.333
<i>Your body still has to do </i><i>the real work.</i>

39:09.709 --> 39:10.834
Your mom's watching the kids.

39:11.667 --> 39:15.333
And the-- the gift shop
was out of flowers.

39:16.709 --> 39:17.750
Teddy, don't do this.

39:17.834 --> 39:19.583
Owen, I love you.

39:19.709 --> 39:20.792
<i>♪ Yeah, wanna love you ♪</i>

39:20.875 --> 39:24.250
I am sorry. I am so sorry.

39:24.333 --> 39:26.375
I will do anything you say to fix this.

39:26.458 --> 39:29.083
I don't want to lose our family.
Owen, please.

39:29.166 --> 39:30.208
Can we just--

39:30.291 --> 39:31.834
Please don't go. Ple-- Owen,

39:31.917 --> 39:34.333
let's just talk about this. Owen.

39:34.417 --> 39:37.333
-[music stops]
-What did I do, Teddy?

39:37.417 --> 39:39.959
What did I do
to make you hate me this much?

39:40.041 --> 39:42.208
When I cheated on Cristina,
it was because I hated her.

39:42.291 --> 39:44.458
-I was enraged, so--
-I don't-- I don't hate you.

39:44.542 --> 39:46.000
That's-- That's not what this was.

39:46.083 --> 39:47.500
Then what?
Because I've spent the last few weeks

39:47.583 --> 39:49.291
trying to comprehend why
you would do that, and I can't.

39:49.375 --> 39:51.000
I don't know. It was a mistake.

39:51.083 --> 39:53.291
It was-- It was a stupid mistake.
That's all.

39:55.417 --> 39:56.542
He asked you to run away with him.

39:56.625 --> 39:57.667
And I said no.

39:57.750 --> 39:59.500
No! No, you didn't!

39:59.583 --> 40:01.625
'Cause I listened to it.
I listened to it almost 100 times.

40:01.709 --> 40:04.542
He asks you to run away,
and you don't say no.

40:04.625 --> 40:06.250
You don't say that you don't want to.

40:06.333 --> 40:08.083
You don't say that you can't
because you love me

40:08.166 --> 40:09.542
or even because you have a family.

40:09.625 --> 40:11.542
You just say, "I'm marrying Owen,"

40:12.291 --> 40:14.417
like it's j-- like it's just
some kind of fate

40:14.500 --> 40:17.542
that you just... accepted.

40:17.625 --> 40:19.041
Look at me.

40:19.125 --> 40:20.041
<i>♪ Once in a while ♪</i>

40:20.125 --> 40:22.625
[Meredith] <i>An army of different cells</i>
<i>comes in to build new tissue.</i>

40:22.709 --> 40:23.875
<i>♪ I see myself ♪</i>

40:23.959 --> 40:25.333
I want to be with <i>you.</i>

40:26.583 --> 40:28.250
[sighs tearfully]

40:28.333 --> 40:31.542
I love our family.

40:31.625 --> 40:33.333
I love you. ♪ By the future or the past ♪

40:35.208 --> 40:39.166
[Meredith] <i>And eventually,</i>
<i>you've produced </i><i>enough collagen to heal.</i>

40:39.250 --> 40:40.291
-Owen.
-I can't. I'm sorry.

40:40.375 --> 40:41.917
-Teddy...
-Owen, please don't go.

40:42.000 --> 40:43.083
Owen, please.

40:43.166 --> 40:44.250
<i>♪ Once in a while ♪</i>

40:44.333 --> 40:46.083
-Owen, please wait.
-[engine starts]

40:46.166 --> 40:47.417
Please don't-- Owen!

40:47.500 --> 40:48.959
Wait! Wait!

40:51.208 --> 40:52.625
[Meredith] <i>At least that's the plan.</i>

40:54.083 --> 40:56.875
<i>Don't get me wrong, </i><i>I'm not saying</i>

40:57.041 --> 40:59.083
<i>you shouldn't obsess </i><i>about technique.</i>

40:59.166 --> 41:00.333
<i>Please, obsess.</i>

41:00.417 --> 41:05.000
<i>♪ They disappear ♪</i>

41:05.083 --> 41:06.375
[Hayes] No. No!

41:06.834 --> 41:08.917
Grey! Grey!

41:09.000 --> 41:10.917
Grey, Grey, can you hear me?

41:11.000 --> 41:12.000
Somebody help me!

41:12.083 --> 41:13.417
[Meredith]
<i>Because even one mistake...</i>

41:13.500 --> 41:15.417
Careful. Careful. I got her head.

41:15.500 --> 41:19.000
I need rapid response, oxygen,
and a gurney now! Go! Hurry up!

41:19.083 --> 41:21.917
Can you hear me, Grey?
Grey, come on. Stay with me, Grey.

41:22.000 --> 41:23.583
I'm here, don't worry. It'll be OK.

41:23.667 --> 41:24.834
[Meredith] <i>One slip...</i>

41:24.917 --> 41:29.166
<i>♪ Deep enough to believe ♪</i>

41:29.250 --> 41:32.000
<i>...can cost a lot of blood.</i>

41:32.083 --> 41:33.208
[man echoing] Meredith!

41:33.291 --> 41:35.750
<i>♪ If every breath is sacred ♪</i>

41:35.834 --> 41:37.208
Meredith!

41:39.208 --> 41:40.375
Oh, my God.

41:41.417 --> 41:42.417
Meredith!

41:43.291 --> 41:47.208
<i>♪ Deep enough to feel something ♪</i>

41:48.333 --> 41:53.542
<i>♪ Deep enough to believe ♪</i>

41:53.625 --> 41:58.083
<i>♪ That every breath is sacred ♪</i>

41:58.959 --> 42:03.542
<i>♪ God, I want to breathe ♪</i>

42:04.375 --> 42:05.250
Meredith!

42:05.333 --> 42:07.208
<i>♪ Deep enough to feel something ♪</i>

42:07.291 --> 42:08.542
Derek.

42:09.417 --> 42:14.625
<i>♪ Please show me how to breathe ♪</i>
